    <h4 class="text-info">The Lepchas Or Rongpas</h4>
    <p>
        The Inhabitants Of Sikkim Are Of Mongolian Origin And Have Been Supplanted By The Virile Nepalese Through Inter-Marriage. Their White Complexion, Tinged With Yellow, The Women Have Graceful Features And Wear Heavy Ear-Rings And Necklaces Studded With Turquoise And Coral. Flowing Hair Woven Into Plaited Pigtails Tops Their Graceful Dress, Reminiscent Of The Roman Gladiators. They Are Buddhists And Under The Influence Of Their Priests.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">The Nepalese</h4>
    <p>
        They Are The Dominant People And Are Divided Into Different Castes, Speaking Various Dialects. The Short Mongolian Type Nepalese, The Gorkhas. They Carry The Traditional Weapon, The Khukri-A Curved Ornamental Knife Put To Every Conceivable Use. They Brought With Them, Hinduism. There Are Also The Gurungs, Magars, Rais, Tamangs And Newars. The Magars Are Also Sub-Divided Into The Ranas & Thapas.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">The Newars</h4>
    <p>
        Newars Are The Original Inhabitants Of The Nepal Valley Possessing Their Own Language, Script And Literature. Besides Being Good Painters, They Are Also Wood-Carvers, Sculptors And Metal Workers.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">The Bhutias</h4>
    <p>
        The Bhutias Are Divided Into Tibetan, Bhutan, Dharma And Sikkim Bhutias.
    </p>
